# =============================================================================
# File: /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/README.cluster-architecture
# =============================================================================
# Purpose:
#   Document the high-level architecture of the k3s cluster, including:
#     - Node roles
#     - Network layout
#     - Build pipeline
#     - Automation boundaries
#
# Node Roles:
#   kubenode1:
#     - Builder node
#     - distcc client
#     - Kernel compilation host
#
#   kubenode2â€“kubenode7:
#     - distccd servers
#     - k3s worker nodes
#
# Network Layout:
#   - All nodes use FQDNs under .home.lab
#   - Subnet: 192.168.29.0/24
#   - DNS resolution handled by home router
#
# Build Pipeline:
#   1. Builder compiles kernel using distcc.
#   2. Ansible deploys kernel artifacts.
#   3. Nodes reboot sequentially.
#
# Automation Boundaries:
#   - 'builder' compiles kernels.
#   - 'ansible' deploys kernels.
#   - distccd runs on worker nodes.
#
# Notes:
#   - This file provides the architectural overview for future maintainers.
# =============================================================================
